MUNSIEVILLE residents cheered yesterday when Police Minister Fikile Mbalula announced he would deal with local cops who were corrupt. Two station commanders from Kagiso and Krugersdorp in Mogale City have already been moved following an outcry from the community. People took to the streets a week ago claiming local cops were working with criminals. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvx282Jualuiu2WfT5uPxGCwiqW3ri1lBFhiK7eLkl2Qhwlu1yKB9_BpRC_trFck0VKtAG0LQf-9Rz9lZi_K1KYhyxucSNXDwZwxXsWBNsKhUp2bvK-NoBnVphz7f32S6J3xarU6xawRnNnvxB-Zbxc2d7-UpaYMXC4C395iOIPVo8_6EMWOCDNgs4Lu0109nkidQwDCQ0BJQz-_1igrDorVvgIm2qR9TdmhQDDlRQGFy_pOGe1HXFJ2C8AL0PnEVn6BsTQD8OuuOHBECIF6o6-kHLb57M\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzCGGBjls943wEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
